metadata.title: USDA PSD Marketing Year Reference
metadata.source: USDA Foreign Agricultural Service PSD Database
metadata.description: Comprehensive mapping of country/commodity combinations to official USDA marketing years and trade years for agricultural data alignment

usage_notes.my_begin_month: Month (1-12) when the local marketing year begins
usage_notes.my_end_month: Month (1-12) when the local marketing year ends (derived: begin_month - 1 with wrap)
usage_notes.ty_begin_month: Month (1-12) when the standardized trade year begins for global comparisons
usage_notes.ty_end_month: Month (1-12) when the trade year ends
usage_notes.my_label_format: Example label format; for Southern Hemisphere summer crops, the SECOND year indicates MY start
usage_notes.southern_hemisphere_rule: For Brazil/Argentina soybeans and corn, MY 2024/25 starts in calendar year 2025, not 2024

trade_year_conventions.period: Calendar Year (Jan-Dec of second year in label)

marketing_years.notes: Calendar year; includes NFDM and WMP
Feb-Jan local; SECOND YEAR labeling (MY 2024/25 starts Feb 2025)
Mar-Feb; SECOND YEAR labeling (MY 2024/25 starts Mar 2025)
Jul-Jun; winter wheat, first year labeling
Apr-Mar; unique to Brazil cane harvest
Apr-Mar local; SECOND YEAR labeling; PSD often adjusts to Oct-Sep TY
Mar-Feb; SECOND YEAR labeling (MY 2024/25 starts Mar 2025)
Oct-Sep; harvest Nov-Jan; first year labeling
Jul-Jun; same as TY; world's largest exporter
May-Apr; SECOND YEAR labeling (MY 2024/25 starts May 2025)
Apr-Mar; second year labeling; major exporter
